---
const education = [
    {
        institution: 'Universidade de Santiago de Compostela',
        degree: 'Dual BSc in Mathematics & Computer Engineering',
        years: '2020 - Present'
    },
    {
        institution: 'University of Łódź',
        degree: 'Erasmus+ Exchange Program',
        years: 'Autumn 2023 - Winter 2024'
    }
];
---

<section class="py-20 animate-fade-in-up">
    <h2 class="mb-12 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-100 sm:text-4xl transition-colors duration-300">
        About Me & Technical Trajectory
    </h2>
    
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-zinc-400 lg:col-span-2 transition-colors duration-300">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-200 transition-colors duration-300">My Background</h3>
            <p>
                Hello! My name is Iago Fernández Perlo, and from a very young age, I have had a profound interest in computers, often dismantling and reassembling old PC hardware to understand how physical components interact. This early hands-on exploration sparked a passion that naturally led me toward the academic intersection of logic and systems engineering.
            </p>
            <p>
                During my secondary education, I developed a strict foundation in algorithmic logic by actively participating in regional mathematical competitions, including the national Mathematical Olympiad and LigaMat. As I delved deeper into computer science, I quickly realized that achieving maximum efficiency required a solid understanding of the underlying mathematics. My trajectory is defined by this continuous search for optimal computational models and their low-level implementation.
            </p>
            <p>
                To complement my focus on system architecture, I have proactively expanded my knowledge of network security. I completed specialized coursework through INCIBE and participate in university and regional Capture The Flag (CTF) events. While I treat these primarily as practical learning exercises, they provide invaluable hands-on experience in identifying vulnerabilities and understanding the critical importance of secure infrastructure design.
            </p>
            <p>
                Currently, I am heavily focused on concurrent architectures, high-performance computing, and the intricate infrastructure required for AI. I thrive on challenges that demand minimizing temporal and spatial complexity in low-latency environments.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-200 transition-colors duration-300">Academic Foundation</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                {education.map(edu => (
                    <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-zinc-700 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-800 p-5 shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md dark:hover:shadow-blue-900/10">
                        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-100 transition-colors duration-300">{edu.institution}</p>
                        <p class="mt-1 text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 transition-colors duration-300">{edu.degree}</p>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-zinc-500 transition-colors duration-300">{edu.years}</p>
                    </div>
                ))}
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>